She has graced our small screens for years now and has built a name for herself as one of Mzansi's most talented actresses. The award-wining actress played Tshidi in etv's prime-time soapie. She has come along way after suffering from depression, even saying she didn't see herself living beyond the year 2001. “There was a time I never saw myself living beyond 2001.” These are the chilling words of actress Nokuthula Ledwaba, last week as she spoke about her struggles with depression and anxiety," she told Independent Online earlier this year. But, thank God she lived beyond that and she slayed when she recently starred in Mzansi Magic's hit drama series Ubomama 